Am going to try this tonight but thought I'd leave this hint behind...Cut up 3-4 sweet onions into thin slices and put them in your crock pot with 1/2 stick of butter ans leave on low for 10-13 hours - the result is the easiest caramelized onions (although the house will stink to high heaven ;)) I package them up and freeze them and use them in recipes, quesadillas on pizza, burgers...

